On Sun, 7 Mar 2004, Tom and Thanh wrote:

> Mark Dearing just mentioned using throwout bearing clips with a loop that
> allows them to be safety wired on. Contact Mark for the address where he
> gets them.

Almost all clips have a loop.  The really old ones don't, but I haven't
seen any for a very long time.

Safety wiring works.  While you're at it, safety-wire the circlip that
positions the throwout shaft.  It can slip and cause mischief.

